1
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:18,820
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:24,096
<i>[Episode 16]</i>

3
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:33,796
Aunty A'Gui, are you done with your chores?

4
00:01:33,796 --> 00:01:36,780
Coming! All you do is hurry me.

5
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,412
Always asking me to hurry up.

6
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,180
Why is the table in a mess again?

7
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:44,540
Remember to clean it up.

8
00:01:44,540 --> 00:01:45,500
Okay.

9
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,660
What's this?

10
00:01:46,660 --> 00:01:48,660
Don't touch it. It's expensive.

11
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:51,760
Come on, Aunty A'Gui. Please have a seat.

12
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:59,100
Aunty A'Gui. Mare's milk.

13
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:01,244
Mare's milk?

14
00:02:01,244 --> 00:02:03,360
Did you get it from A'Yao's horse ranch?

15
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,060
Bingo.

16
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,600
I'm aiming for a limited edition series.

17
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,680
I brewed this cup just for you.

18
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,280
Have a taste.

19
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:19,840
This is golden silk black tea.

20
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:23,480
I'm using this as a tea base to pair with mare's milk.

21
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:26,952
Based on my understanding of you,

22
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:31,880
I'll brew a special cup of milk tea

23
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:35,908
with my ideal golden ratio.

24
00:02:35,908 --> 00:02:37,956
What an honor.

25
00:02:43,420 --> 00:02:46,080
- Have a taste.
- Okay.

26
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,360
Mr. Ma, I'm done.

27
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:51,100
Personally, I like green plum tea the most.

28
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,240
It has a milder taste than the sourness of lemons,

29
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,484
so I gave it a nine out of ten.

30
00:02:58,140 --> 00:03:01,520
But this is based on my personal preference.

31
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,860
I don't know much about tea.

32
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:04,620
It's right to trust your feelings.

33
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:08,100
The most important aspect is to suit your taste.

34
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:11,980
Why do customers come to the store?

35
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:13,900
They want to enjoy the service.

36
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:17,464
Of course, they can come once or twice for the novelty.

37
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:20,380
But what keeps customers?

38
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:22,980
It's the product.

39
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,220
Hongdou,

40
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:29,784
are you sure you don't like milk tea?

41
00:03:29,784 --> 00:03:31,100
I not particularly fond of it.

42
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,612
I prefer pure tea over other drinks.

43
00:03:33,612 --> 00:03:35,520
Milk tea is just too expensive, isn't it?

44
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:39,140
It could easily cost ¥20 to ¥30 per cup.

45
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:41,820
Gosh. How much is a cup?

46
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:42,980
Around ¥30.

47
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:44,680
¥30?

48
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,960
Just for a small cup like this?

49
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,080
No, that's not it.

50
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,680
This is a limited-edition drink.

51
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,480
The price of this would be more than ¥30.

52
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:53,640
Why is it so expensive?

53
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:55,684
Is there gold in it?

54
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:58,180
Aunty A'Gui.

55
00:03:58,180 --> 00:04:00,180
Actually, this is a fabulous idea.

56
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:03,856
I can consider adding gold leaves to them,

57
00:04:03,856 --> 00:04:07,360
but I'll have to revise the prices again.

58
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:11,684
Mr. Ma, I reckon you should quit selling milk tea.

59
00:04:11,684 --> 00:04:13,420
Just rob people on the streets.

60
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:16,200
You'll get the money faster.

61
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:21,640
I slave from morning to night daily for just ¥50,

62
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,724
but you're charging ¥30 for just a cup of milk tea.

63
00:04:24,724 --> 00:04:26,728
I'd never buy it.

64
00:04:26,728 --> 00:04:29,428
Aunty A'Gui, here's the thing.

65
00:04:29,428 --> 00:04:32,796
The milk tea isn't expensive,

66
00:04:32,796 --> 00:04:35,920
but I have to cover the costs of the rent, utility bills,

67
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:38,260
and manpower in the price.

68
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:40,268
Let me ask you this.

69
00:04:40,268 --> 00:04:44,496
Where will you find so many suckers willing to throw money at you?

70
00:04:44,496 --> 00:04:45,640
Hold on.

71
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,940
Aunty A'Gui, you can't call them suckers.

72
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:52,040
- People have consumption needs.
- Yes.

73
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:55,021
Look. A cup of milk tea costs ¥20 to ¥30.

74
00:04:55,021 --> 00:04:58,040
It's an affordable price for ordinary customers to enjoy once in a while.

75
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:02,044
However, it's a hefty expense if someone drinks them daily.

76
00:05:02,044 --> 00:05:06,664
That's true, but we have a membership card.

77
00:05:06,664 --> 00:05:08,360
But there are people like me.

78
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:12,360
The consumer trap of bragging about a gift of milk tea in autumn doesn't work on us.

79
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,520
We're the minority.

80
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,680
Mr. Ma, you can ignore me.

81
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:18,400
Of course. If the shop has a nice environment,

82
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,160
good service, and a distinctive vibe,

83
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:24,600
your store will be my first choice for a business meeting.

84
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:29,268
After all, tons of people want to support domestic brands now.

85
00:05:29,268 --> 00:05:32,920
Hongdou, you're offering great help,

86
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:36,176
especially in terms of product promotion

87
00:05:36,176 --> 00:05:39,868
and increasing customer retention.

88
00:05:39,868 --> 00:05:44,308
We haven't done enough consumer research.

89
00:05:44,308 --> 00:05:46,630
I'm glad I could be of help.

90
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:49,980
That's payment for your tea.

91
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:52,360
You can enjoy free tea on me at any time.

92
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,916
If I were you,

93
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:57,720
I'd buy milk from the supermarket and brew my own black tea at home.

94
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:00,932
That's the same, isn't it?

95
00:06:00,932 --> 00:06:03,420
I'd never fall for your tricks.

96
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:07,240
He specializes in swindling rich people of their money.

97
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:09,501
Don't say that. This isn't a scam.

98
00:06:09,501 --> 00:06:11,828
This is a business,

99
00:06:11,828 --> 00:06:14,724
and businesses have their respective consumer groups.

100
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:23,044
Yes, certainly. Hongdou's right.

101
00:06:23,044 --> 00:06:26,480
Am I being a nuisance here?

102
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:32,300
Look. Mr. Ma is treating me to his expensive milk tea,

103
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,200
but I said such unpleasant things.

104
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,740
I'm sorry, Mr. Ma.

105
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:37,340
It's nothing.

106
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:40,000
I should learn from the mynas.

107
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:44,560
Whenever I see you, I'll say, "May wealth shower upon you! Delicious!"

108
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,360
Please don't.

109
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:49,080
Aunty A'Gui, you have to stay true to who you are.

110
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:53,412
Do you know why I like and adore you?

111
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:58,196
It's because of your unfaltering honesty.

112
00:06:58,196 --> 00:06:59,760
You always speak your mind.

113
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,980
You're frank and outspoken.

114
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:03,540
I love you to bits.

115
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,440
What a glib talker.

116
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,020
All he does is flatter me.

117
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:10,840
Just one utterance tells me you aren't a decent man.

118
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,200
All right, enough.

119
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,440
I still have unfinished chores.

120
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,040
I don't have time to chat with you.

121
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:21,932
This tastes pretty good.

122
00:07:21,932 --> 00:07:24,280
- I'm off.
- Okay.

123
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:26,760
Come here for more once you're done.

124
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:31,440
Damai, aren't you done typing yet?

125
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,900
Almost done.

126
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:48,624
Are you writing your graduation thesis?

127
00:07:48,624 --> 00:07:50,820
Look at this. Let me take a look.

128
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:56,000
Damai, are you writing a novel about tea leaves?

129
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,952
What's this about the taboo love

130
00:07:59,952 --> 00:08:02,360
between soy milk and Pu'er tea?

131
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:09,680
Damai, this is great.

132
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,360
What?

133
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,560
Can you write a story for me?

134
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,460
Nope.

135
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:18,000
It's a very simple story.

136
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,680
Let's personify soy milk and make a comic—

137
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:23,880
I mean you need to pay me.

138
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,560
We're adults.

139
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,880
There's no such thing as a free story,

140
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:31,780
but I can give you a discount.

141
00:08:31,780 --> 00:08:34,000
You startled me.

142
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,120
- Isn't it just money? Name your price.
- Deal.

143
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,300
I look forward to working with you!

144
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:43,880
I'll write it right away.

145
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,748
Hello? My parcel?

146
00:08:47,748 --> 00:08:49,340
Just leave it at the collection kiosk.

147
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:51,040
Okay, thank you.

148
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:52,700
I'm going to pick up my parcel.

149
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:54,500
Go ahead.

150
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:18,260
<i>Master, hit me again.</i>

151
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:19,932
<i>Let's go!</i>

152
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:30,120
<i>Master! Master!</i>

153
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,080
<i>What?</i>

154
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,060
<i>What are you carving?</i>

155
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:36,120
<i>Don't you have eyes?</i>

156
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:40,004
<i>We're customizing this wooden lotus carving for a hotel.</i>

157
00:09:40,004 --> 00:09:41,700
<i>Check out my master's skills.</i>

158
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,768
<i>Intricate. Pure art.</i>

159
00:09:44,768 --> 00:09:48,792
<i>Why don't you do your work instead of fawning over me?</i>

160
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,000
<i>[Hahaha! Master is shy!]
Stop filming me!</i>

161
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,220
<i>[Master is so fierce]
Film yourself! Goodness.</i>

162
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:56,800
<i>Master, the fans want to see you.</i>

163
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,920
<i>[Xia Xia is on the brink of getting walloped]
They think you're impressive.</i>

164
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,760
<i>They think I'm impressive?</i>

165
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:01,800
<i>[Master is so focused]
Get lost.</i>

166
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,900
<i>[Hahahahaha]
Stop filming! Stop filming me!</i>

167
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:17,820
<i>[Xia Xia deserves a beating for his mischief]
Master! I have a gift for you.</i>

168
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:19,180
<i>I don't want it.</i>

169
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:22,588
<i>Master, give me your hand.</i>

170
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:27,680
<i>What is it?</i>

171
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:32,280
<i>Darned brat! Stop there!</i>

172
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,520
<i>- Run!
- Stop!</i>

173
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,240
<i>You... Stop running!</i>

174
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,960
<i>Stop right there!</i>

175
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,540
<i>Don't run!</i>

176
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:44,436
I love this "Master, Hit Me Again" series.

177
00:10:44,436 --> 00:10:47,820
The series, "Senior, Teach Me," was also pretty good.

178
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:50,840
It's really hilarious to watch your master wallop you.

179
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,480
My master really hits me.

180
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,180
It hurts.

181
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:56,320
Take it easy with the coffee. It's late in the afternoon.

182
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,440
You won't be able to sleep at night.

183
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,320
I still need to work tonight.

184
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,840
When have you been this diligent?

185
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,860
My master got me more jobs for more practice.

186
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:07,940
I'll set a good example for my juniors.

187
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,880
Our Xia Xia is a sensible boy now. You're all grown up.

188
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,620
Stop it.

189
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:25,840
Why do you look so pleased?

190
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:29,120
Because I have someone picking me up, too.

191
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:34,880
Be honest.

192
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:37,480
You're a homebody, but you insist on picking me up from work.

193
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,640
Are you sure you aren't forcing yourself to do this?

194
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:45,204
I... I know sitting for too long is bad for my health.

195
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,620
I'm experienced with that.

196
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:54,248
When your life is plagued with agony,

197
00:11:54,248 --> 00:11:57,712
only negative thoughts occupy your mind all the time.

198
00:11:57,712 --> 00:12:00,600
It does nothing in resolving problems.

199
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:04,668
At such moments, as long as we take a stroll outside,

200
00:12:04,668 --> 00:12:06,604
chat with others,

201
00:12:06,604 --> 00:12:08,760
breathe in the fresh air,

202
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:11,000
bask in the sun,

203
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,936
and enjoy delicious food,

204
00:12:12,936 --> 00:12:16,000
we'll slowly feel rejuvenated.

205
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,020
I'll listen to your advice.

206
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:28,640
I'll come out more often, bask in the sun, and enjoy good food.

207
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:29,580
Okay.

208
00:12:29,580 --> 00:12:31,840
Well, what are we having for dinner tonight?

209
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,680
What would you like to eat? I'll cook for you.

210
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,460
Let me think.

211
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:41,860
- Uncle.
- A'Yao.

212
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,948
Is she still asleep?

213
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:51,640
Xu Hongdou!

214
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,380
Were you woken up by the birds?

215
00:13:24,460 --> 00:13:27,760
Dad, are you going to fetch water?

216
00:13:31,660 --> 00:13:34,472
She's a tenant in the courtyard.

217
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,500
I can see that.

218
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,800
Blackie.

219
00:14:11,220 --> 00:14:13,780
Blackie.

220
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:15,384
Jiahui.

221
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,640
What are you eating?

222
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:32,080
Uncle!

223
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,280
You're back!

224
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,080
Xiao Hu.

225
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,200
Hello, Uncle.

226
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,436
When did you come back?

227
00:14:38,436 --> 00:14:41,360
It's the death anniversary of A'Yao's grandpa. I came to sweep his tomb.

228
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,980
- Are things going well at home?
- yes.

229
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:46,480
Has A'Yuan been well-behaved lately?

230
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,340
Yes.

231
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:49,060
He's started to study.

232
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:50,440
That's great.

233
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:53,280
A while back, Chairman Xie was worried sick about him.

234
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:57,612
- Teenage boys are—
- How's your new song coming along?

235
00:14:58,340 --> 00:15:00,040
Uncle, I haven't written any songs lately.

236
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:01,800
Once I write a new one, I'll send it to you immediately.

237
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:04,100
You can listen to it and perk up while you're out on deliveries.

238
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,440
No, thanks.

239
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:09,500
We don't listen to such whining when delivering goods.

240
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:12,940
Can't you write something like Phoenix Legend's songs?

241
00:15:12,940 --> 00:15:15,492
That'll pump me up!

242
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:20,300
We don't work with the same genre, Uncle.

243
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,800
You can change your style.

244
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,320
Write songs that common folks like us would enjoy.

245
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:26,420
Such as...

246
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:29,580
♪ <i>I swim like a fish in a pond</i> ♪

247
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:33,236
That one. That's so uplifting.

248
00:15:33,236 --> 00:15:37,680
A'Yuan's mom spends two hours with that daily.

249
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:39,300
She has so much fun.

250
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:41,640
Those songs are great.

251
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:44,080
Got it, Uncle. I... I'll try my best.

252
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:46,440
Okay. Give your all.

253
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:48,660
I'll leave you to your day.

254
00:15:50,180 --> 00:15:52,480
- Goodbye, Uncle.
- Get on with your work.

255
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,820
Take care, Uncle.

256
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,340
Aunty Hua.

257
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:21,521
Huzi's parents! Are you going back to Guangzhou?

258
00:16:21,521 --> 00:16:22,900
Yeah, things are busy in the factory.

259
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:24,820
The boss called and urged us to go back.

260
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:25,980
It's good to be busy.

261
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:27,720
They're charged per piece of clothing.

262
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:30,676
More work means more money.

263
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,236
Where are you two headed?

264
00:16:33,236 --> 00:16:35,780
We're going to pick someone up.

265
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:38,560
<i>[Woodfish Sundry Store]</i>

266
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:41,081
Sister, I want the pineapple flavor.

267
00:16:41,081 --> 00:16:42,720
I want the peach flavor.

268
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:44,320
I also want the pineapple flavor.

269
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:45,720
I want the peach flavor.

270
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,120
Okay.

271
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,040
Here you go.

272
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:53,120
- Thank you, Sister!
- Thank you!

273
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,560
You're welcome.

274
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:10,160
Tuotuo, thank you for treating us to popsicles.

275
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,920
Don't worry, I have money.

276
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:14,480
My dad and mom are leaving in a few days.

277
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:17,840
They give me pocket money every day.

278
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:18,800
That's awesome.

279
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,960
Every time your mom and dad come back,

280
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:25,012
they bring you so much good food and toys.

281
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:28,440
I want my dad to sell barbecue in Kunming, too.

282
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:33,200
Ask Uncle A'Yao to convince him to earn more money outside this town.

283
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,320
Uncle won't do that.

284
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:38,796
He wants everyone from the village to return.

285
00:17:38,796 --> 00:17:41,512
Uncle A'Yao's a big baddie.

286
00:17:41,512 --> 00:17:43,240
A big baddie.

287
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:49,884
Why are all four of you here?

288
00:17:49,884 --> 00:17:52,000
Huzi, your mom is leaving.

289
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,960
Why are you still eating a popsicle here?

290
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:55,768
Where's my mom?

291
00:17:55,768 --> 00:17:58,460
She's waiting at the entrance of the town.

292
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:01,632
Mom! Mom!

293
00:18:01,632 --> 00:18:03,984
- Mom!
- Let's go!

294
00:18:03,984 --> 00:18:06,840
<i>Mom! Mom!</i>

295
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:12,420
- Huzi!
- Huzi!

296
00:18:12,420 --> 00:18:14,112
Huzi!

297
00:18:14,112 --> 00:18:16,380
Aunty Hua, aren't you leaving with Honghong?

298
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:18,440
I'd love to, but what can I even do there?

299
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:22,960
- Take care of yourself, Mom.
- You too.

300
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,800
Don't overwork yourself. Get more rest.

301
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,920
Give me a hug.

302
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,120
You too. Take care of yourself.

303
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:28,881
Don't work too hard.

304
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:32,280
Every time I return to Beijing,

305
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,380
my mom would say the same thing to me.

306
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:41,280
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

307
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:42,620
Oh no, Huzi is here.

308
00:18:42,620 --> 00:18:43,740
Mom!

309
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:45,380
Huzi!

310
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:47,361
Get in the car. Come on, get in the car.

311
00:18:47,361 --> 00:18:48,460
- Huzi!
- You can't go over!

312
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:50,441
Don't run! You won't be able to leave if you go over!

313
00:18:50,441 --> 00:18:51,540
Come back!

314
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:53,080
Leave him to me! Get in the car!

315
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:55,532
Quickly, get in the car!

316
00:18:57,760 --> 00:19:00,361
- Huzi!
- Huzi, your mom will be back soon.

317
00:19:00,361 --> 00:19:03,521
Don't run! I'm here with you.

318
00:19:03,521 --> 00:19:05,852
Darling, don't run.

319
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:14,020
♫ <i>Set sail when it's windy</i> ♫

320
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:21,120
♫ <i>The reflection of clouds, the changing moon,
and the starry sky</i> ♫

321
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:25,440
♫ <i>Disoriented footsteps will gradually be erased</i> ♫

322
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,580
Do you know why Xiao Huang and I are working so hard?

323
00:19:29,580 --> 00:19:30,940
That's the reason.

324
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,880
I'll buy you an Ultraman, okay?

325
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,410
I'll buy you an Ultraman and snacks.

326
00:19:35,410 --> 00:19:40,820
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

327
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:44,080
Huzi! Come on! Get up!

328
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,401
It's fine. There, there.

329
00:19:46,401 --> 00:19:48,680
It's okay. All right. It's okay.

330
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:51,516
I'll take you to feed the horses, all right?

331
00:19:51,516 --> 00:19:53,540
I'll buy you popsicles, all right?

332
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:55,500
Don't cry.

333
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,412
There, there.

334
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:00,580
It's okay. Aunty Hua, it's okay.

335
00:20:00,580 --> 00:20:07,260
♫ <i>When the wind rises, the sky will be cloudless</i> ♫

336
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:12,520
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

337
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,320
There, there.

338
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:19,320
I'll take you to feed the horses and buy you popsicles.

339
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,740
- Hello.
- Hello. Are you Sunzi and Xiao Fang?

340
00:20:24,741 --> 00:20:27,000
- Yes, hello. I'm Sunzi.
- Hello, I'm Xu Hongdou.

341
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,920
Huang Xinxin's in a meeting. She asked Chairman Xie and me to pick you up.

342
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:33,300
Chairman... That's Chairman Xie.

343
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:40,100
Uncle Siping is here.

344
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:42,000
- The old man is here?
- Is it too late to flee?

345
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,500
Aunty, are you busy?

346
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:46,180
Gezi!

347
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:48,120
Uncle, you're here.

348
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:51,060
Ye Sen, I've been looking for you.

349
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:54,084
I just took a look around your little warehouse.

350
00:20:54,084 --> 00:20:56,120
Xiaoyue said you have a day off today.

351
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,820
Yes.

352
00:20:57,820 --> 00:20:59,660
Are you out having fun?

353
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,800
Gezi asked me to help her. Colleagues should help each other.

354
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,360
Yes, I asked him to help me.

355
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:06,976
Well, you can get on with your work.

356
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:24,748
Uncle, how can we help you?

357
00:21:24,748 --> 00:21:27,400
I just want to have a casual chat.

358
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,080
Don't mind me.

359
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:40,200
A'Yao's helping Heshun renovate the wood carving workshop and promote it.

360
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,300
Is it for free?

361
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:46,120
Why are you eyeing him?

362
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:50,900
Your handicraft website is also selling wood carvings from the wood carving workshop, right?

363
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:53,740
Is A'Yao just helping them,

364
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:55,920
or is he receiving a share of the money?

365
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:58,360
Ye Sen, Uncle's asking you a question.

366
00:21:58,360 --> 00:21:59,540
Don't ask me. My leg hurts.

367
00:21:59,540 --> 00:22:01,340
It doesn't.

368
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:06,004
You can't possibly be clueless.

369
00:22:06,580 --> 00:22:09,800
Ye Sen, you designed the website.

370
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,740
Gezi, you were the one who posted the products. Right?

371
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:17,196
Well... I guess...

372
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,820
he's helping them.

373
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:21,816
That seems right.

374
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:25,180
He's helping them.

375
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:29,533
So, he's free labor for Heshun.

376
00:22:33,580 --> 00:22:35,060
I'll let you get on with your work.

377
00:22:35,060 --> 00:22:36,240
Goodbye, Uncle.

378
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:38,780
- Aunty, I'm leaving.
- See you.

379
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:41,000
Thank goodness he's gone.

380
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,540
Let's get to work so we can eat sooner.

381
00:22:43,540 --> 00:22:45,780
We sparked a new problem again.

382
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,156
<i>[To Freedom]</i>

383
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:18,360
Try it.

384
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,660
Nice.

385
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:34,340
This is more like it.

386
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,880
When you have nothing to do,

387
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:39,296
come out for some sunlight.

388
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:41,900
Doesn't this feel great?

389
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:45,984
It's beneficial to your writing as well.

390
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,400
One more thing.

391
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:52,820
When you're free, spend more time chatting with me.

392
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:56,252
That's beneficial to a song composition.

393
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:04,180
The wind has risen.

394
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:10,200
I just came up with some lyrics.

395
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:16,328
♪ <i>Blow, blow it away</i> ♪

396
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,428
Why is he back again?

397
00:25:20,428 --> 00:25:21,980
Who is it?

398
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,264
Phoenix Legend's fan.

399
00:25:24,264 --> 00:25:26,680
Chairman Xie's father.

400
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:28,268
Be careful of him.

401
00:25:28,268 --> 00:25:29,860
I'm going to hide in my room.

402
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:31,040
I'm leaving.

403
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,740
Be careful.

404
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,640
Who are you looking for?

405
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:04,980
You must be Xu Hongdou, right?

406
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:06,400
Yes, I am.

407
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,168
I'm Xie Zhiyao's dad.

408
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:12,740
Uncle Xie? Hello.

409
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:14,580
Don't stand. Stay seated.

410
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:17,460
Sit down. Sit.

411
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,120
Bye-bye.

412
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:38,752
Is A'Yuan doing well in school?

413
00:26:38,752 --> 00:26:40,200
He's studying hard now.

414
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,900
Really?

415
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:44,688
That's great.

416
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:48,840
This courtyard is really well decorated.

417
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:50,020
Yeah.

418
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:53,176
Aunty A'Gui's very attentive.

419
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:56,760
Have you gotten used to living here?

420
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,260
I have.

421
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:02,580
One ore two months here is fine,

422
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:04,928
but you'll miss Beijing as time passes.

423
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,400
Perhaps.

424
00:27:15,260 --> 00:27:19,004
Do you have something to say to me?

425
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:23,140
I just happened to see you and came over for a chat.

426
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:24,600
Sure.

427
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:27,480
I heard A'Yao's granny say that

428
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:31,116
A'Yao is all ears to anything you say.

429
00:27:31,116 --> 00:27:32,800
Hold on.

430
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,120
This is probably a misunderstanding.

431
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:38,328
Both of us only speak about the cafe.

432
00:27:38,328 --> 00:27:39,520
That's perfect.

433
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:41,540
I'm talking about the cafe.

434
00:27:41,540 --> 00:27:44,752
Could you give me some suggestions?

435
00:27:44,752 --> 00:27:47,044
Sure, go ahead.

436
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:51,740
Look. Yunmiao is in the countryside.

437
00:27:51,740 --> 00:27:55,496
Youngsters who excel at their studies leave for the cities.

438
00:27:55,496 --> 00:27:58,476
Those who can't study but are quick-witted

439
00:27:58,476 --> 00:28:00,844
buy a car to start a business

440
00:28:00,844 --> 00:28:07,060
in crowded spots like Shuanglang, Xizhou, or the Old Town.

441
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:11,420
Even if we holler our throats dry in a small place like Yunmiao,

442
00:28:11,420 --> 00:28:13,280
only a handful of people will hear us.

443
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:15,740
That's very logical.

444
00:28:15,740 --> 00:28:20,620
But here's my opinion, we can't make such generalizations.

445
00:28:20,620 --> 00:28:23,180
Before those places were developed,

446
00:28:23,180 --> 00:28:26,260
they were also small fishing villages and old towns. Right?

447
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:27,560
Yeah.

448
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:30,728
It's the same with wholesale flowers at the market.

449
00:28:30,728 --> 00:28:32,720
Initially, there were few people in the business.

450
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,580
A small shop can easily grow.

451
00:28:34,580 --> 00:28:37,800
Once the shop flourishes, there'll be more purchases and customers.

452
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:42,620
If there's a good supply flow, flower suppliers will be willing...

453
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:47,100
to offer rare flowers and the best flowers at the best price.

454
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:48,880
With a big shop,

455
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:52,500
there'll be better sales and more customers to bring more profits. The shop will continue expanding.

456
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:57,380
How can small shops that just started out compete with such known shops?

457
00:28:57,820 --> 00:28:58,800
You're absolutely right.

458
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:02,080
- Aren't I?
- But here's what I think.

459
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:05,080
This comparison isn't all.

460
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:09,100
Shops may stock the same items,

461
00:29:09,100 --> 00:29:14,520
but tourist spots offer different scenery in each place.

462
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:16,280
Don't you agree?

463
00:29:17,140 --> 00:29:18,640
Fine.

464
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,360
I won't make such a comparison.

465
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:23,540
Let's talk about something else. Look at A'Yao.

466
00:29:23,540 --> 00:29:25,040
Back then,

467
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:28,040
his mom left this place to work so that he could study.

468
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:32,688
It was so that he could leave this small village and escape poverty.

469
00:29:32,688 --> 00:29:36,100
A'Yao lived up to our expectations and entered a college in Beijing.

470
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:38,660
He got a good job in Beijing that paid him well,

471
00:29:38,660 --> 00:29:40,400
but he insisted on coming back.

472
00:29:40,408 --> 00:29:44,580
He invested all the money he earned here and even ended up with loans.

473
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:47,580
He's just been shoving money down a rabbit hole for years.

474
00:29:47,580 --> 00:29:51,300
Some buses travel through town, but what about this place?

475
00:29:51,300 --> 00:29:55,396
This small village doesn't have tourists.

476
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:58,200
Yes. You're right.

477
00:29:58,260 --> 00:29:59,980
Right?

478
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:05,000
Look. Parents are always far-sighted and thorough when it comes to their children.

479
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,100
That's the way my parents are.

480
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:08,260
Exactly. This is it.

481
00:30:08,260 --> 00:30:11,632
No wonder A'Yao's granny loves you.

482
00:30:11,632 --> 00:30:15,180
A lass like you is pretty impressive.

483
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:20,040
You're smart and a sweet talker.

484
00:30:27,780 --> 00:30:28,760
Uncle,

485
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:32,108
well... were you just unloading your worries

486
00:30:32,108 --> 00:30:38,320
or do you want me to persuade A'Yao to go back to Beijing?

487
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,900
Bingo.

488
00:30:42,580 --> 00:30:47,588
Ever since A'Yap returned, he hasn't benefited in the slightest.

489
00:30:47,588 --> 00:30:50,220
He's everyone's go-to person now.

490
00:30:50,820 --> 00:30:52,360
He has tons of problems weighing him down.

491
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:55,960
What has Xie Heshun's wood carving workshop got to do with him?

492
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,848
Well... Well... and this homestay.

493
00:30:58,848 --> 00:30:59,880
What has this got to do with him?

494
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:02,520
Xiao Huang is the one in charge,

495
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:05,000
but everyone goes to A'Yao to resolve their problems.

496
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,944
That's such a hassle!

497
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,020
You're right,

498
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:12,981
but A'Yao has already invested a lot.

499
00:31:12,981 --> 00:31:17,616
If he leaves now, with all the infrastructure in place,

500
00:31:17,616 --> 00:31:19,640
all his efforts will be in vain.

501
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:22,524
He can sell them.

502
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:25,300
Someone who's willing to take over

503
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:28,572
clearly recognizes the value of these efforts.

504
00:31:28,572 --> 00:31:30,180
Don't you agree?

505
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,252
That's true.

506
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:40,160
Isn't this like a mosquito who flew into a spider's web?

507
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:42,720
It can't escape no matter how hard it tries to fly away.

508
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:45,588
Why did he do all this?

509
00:31:49,380 --> 00:31:53,520
Uncle Xie, do you want to hear my story?

510
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,620
Sure.

511
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:56,000
Here's the thing.

512
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,960
Since I graduated from college, I've been working in Beijing.

513
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:01,860
The hotel industry is particularly hectic.

514
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:04,560
Occasionally, when customers thank me,

515
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:08,328
I also feel a sense of accomplishment and recognition. Right?

516
00:32:08,328 --> 00:32:12,992
But most of the time, I'm just working mechanically.

517
00:32:12,992 --> 00:32:15,460
After working for over a decade,

518
00:32:16,240 --> 00:32:18,720
I shared the same thoughts as most people.

519
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:24,000
I wanted to earn money for a house and a car.

520
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:27,040
With those, I'd be able to settle in Beijing.

521
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:30,260
When I returned to my hometown,

522
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:31,960
my relatives will think I'm very successful. Right?

523
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:33,200
They'll think I'm outstanding.

524
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:37,300
I could be a role model for the younger generation to aspire toward.

525
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:39,340
That's wonderful.

526
00:32:40,300 --> 00:32:42,780
However, I never considered...

527
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:49,572
whether success in the conventional sense is what I really want.

528
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:53,204
Let's take this as an example.

529
00:32:55,100 --> 00:33:00,220
If I only have three months left to live before I leave this world,

530
00:33:01,140 --> 00:33:03,340
what do I really want to do?

531
00:33:03,340 --> 00:33:05,420
What is my dream? What do I want to do?

532
00:33:05,420 --> 00:33:07,680
I never ever thought about these.

533
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:10,240
It has never crossed my mind.

534
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:15,920
However, A'Yao and Xinxin are different.

535
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:20,860
They have a firm ambition and an ideal to fight for.

536
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:25,308
I'm very envious of them.

537
00:33:26,380 --> 00:33:28,564
I admire them.

538
00:33:28,564 --> 00:33:31,660
They aren't selfishly thinking about themselves.

539
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:34,600
Neither do they focus on the immediate present.

540
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:36,630
They have a much further destination in sight,

541
00:33:36,630 --> 00:33:39,380
